### Test Member Login and Dashboard System Integration

### 1. Create Test Member (Development Only)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/test/create-test-member
Content-Type: application/json

### 2. Get Test Credentials
GET http://localhost:8081/api/test/credentials
Content-Type: application/json

### 3. Test Member Registration
POST http://localhost:8081/api/members/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "username": "johndoe",
  "email": "john.doe@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "contact": "1234567890"
}

### 4. Test Member Authentication (Username)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/members/authenticate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testmember",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 5. Test Member Authentication (Email)
POST http://localhost:8081/api/members/authenticate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "test@member.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 6. Get Member Profile (Replace MEMBER_ID with actual ID from authentication)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/members/MEMBER_ID/profile
Content-Type: application/json

### 7. Get Member Dashboard Data (Replace MEMBER_ID with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/members/MEMBER_ID/dashboard
Content-Type: application/json

### 8. Get Member's Active Borrows (Replace MEMBER_ID with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/members/MEMBER_ID/borrows/active
Content-Type: application/json

### 9. Get Member's Fines (Replace MEMBER_ID with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/members/MEMBER_ID/fines
Content-Type: application/json

### 10. Get Member's Outstanding Fine Amount (Replace MEMBER_ID with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/members/MEMBER_ID/fines/outstanding
Content-Type: application/json

### 11. Get Member's Reservations (Replace MEMBER_ID with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/members/MEMBER_ID/reservations
Content-Type: application/json

### 12. Get Member's Notifications (Replace MEMBER_ID with actual ID)
GET http://localhost:8081/api/members/MEMBER_ID/notifications
Content-Type: application/json

### 13. Update Member Profile (Replace MEMBER_ID with actual ID)
PUT http://localhost:8081/api/members/MEMBER_ID/profile
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe Updated",
  "email": "john.updated@example.com",
  "contact": "0987654321"
}

### 14. Test Invalid Authentication
POST http://localhost:8081/api/members/authenticate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "invaliduser",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

### 15. Test Registration with Duplicate Username
POST http://localhost:8081/api/members/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another User",
  "username": "testmember",
  "email": "another@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "contact": "1111111111"
}

### 16. Test Registration with Duplicate Email
POST http://localhost:8081/api/members/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Another User",
  "username": "anotheruser",
  "email": "test@member.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "contact": "1111111111"
}

### Notes for Testing:
# 1. Start the backend server first: cd backendlab && ./mvnw spring-boot:run
# 2. Create test member using endpoint #1
# 3. Use the returned member ID in subsequent requests
# 4. Test the frontend by navigating to http://localhost:3000
# 5. Click "Member" in navigation to go to member login
# 6. Use credentials: username "testmember", password "password123"
# 7. Verify dashboard shows member-specific data

### Expected Frontend Flow:
# 1. User clicks "Member" in navbar → redirects to /member-login
# 2. User can login with username/email and password
# 3. User can click "Register Here" to create new account
# 4. After login, user is redirected to /member/dashboard
# 5. Dashboard shows member-specific data (borrows, fines, etc.)
# 6. All data is filtered to show only the logged-in member's information

### Security Features:
# - Passwords are encrypted using BCrypt
# - Member can only access their own data
# - Authentication required for all member endpoints
# - Username and email uniqueness enforced
# - Input validation on all forms